oke’ from Black American culture – and brings us right up to current-day debates. By examining the political causes that woke capitalism has co-opted, and the social causes that it has not, he argues that this surreptitious extension of capitalism has serious implications for us all.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBusiness and politics. 0aBusiness ethicsxCase studies. 0aBusiness ethics. 0aConsumption (Economics)xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aCorporationsxPolitical aspects. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Government & Business.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z9783111196756oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978152921167240uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529211696?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529211696423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529211696/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2021